                  p KPCC recently won 10 Golden Mike Awards - more than any other radio station - at the 63rd annual Radio & Television News Association of Southern California's awards gala. Mary Plummer (pictured) won Best Light Feature for her story "Urban mashing." For "Anaheim Violence", Corey Moore (pictured) took home the award for Best News Reporting. He also grabbed the prize for Best Sports Reporting.
